1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,054
Three opportunities arrive with different fit,
timing, and delivery risk.

2
00:00:05,054 --> 00:00:08,086
TenderGraph recommends select, review, or pass.

3
00:00:08,086 --> 00:00:11,118
We choose the high-fit clinic tender.

4
00:00:11,118 --> 00:00:14,655
The agent still cannot allocate company resources.

5
00:00:14,655 --> 00:00:18,193
A bid manager must approve the investment.

6
00:00:18,743 --> 00:00:22,173
Approval unlocks evidence-bound requirements and the
bid plan.

7
00:00:22,173 --> 00:00:24,316
Named owners receive dependency-aware tasks.

8
00:00:24,316 --> 00:00:27,745
Compliance remains blocked by an unresolved
certificate review.

9
00:00:27,745 --> 00:00:32,032
Then amendment v2 shortens delivery from 15 to 10
days.

10
00:00:32,032 --> 00:00:36,319
TenderGraph checks all five requirements: 1 changed,
4 remain valid.

11
00:00:36,319 --> 00:00:39,320
Only the two affected tasks are reopened.

12
00:00:39,320 --> 00:00:42,750
A second blocker appears. Final submission remains
disabled.

13
00:00:42,750 --> 00:00:44,893
Release authority is permanently human-only.

14
00:00:45,443 --> 00:00:50,792
The operating layer is proven against a
hash-verified public evaluation.

15
00:00:50,792 --> 00:00:54,537
Every conclusion is bound to exact evidence.

16
00:00:54,537 --> 00:01:00,421
The inspector exposes source, page, quotation,
parser, authority, URL, and hash.

17
00:01:00,421 --> 00:01:04,700
A commission recommendation is not a signed
contract.

18
00:01:05,250 --> 00:01:10,399
The question runs through ChatGPT-authenticated
Codex without an API key.

19
00:01:10,399 --> 00:01:13,489
GPT-5.6 composes only from admitted claims.

20
00:01:13,489 --> 00:01:17,608
The trace retains the model and Session ID.

21
00:01:17,608 --> 00:01:22,242
Fifteen code-owned gates reject invention, evidence
swaps, scope contamination,

22
00:01:22,242 --> 00:01:24,302
leakage, and incomplete output.

23
00:01:24,852 --> 00:01:28,705
A new official PDF becomes hashed, addressable
evidence.

24
00:01:28,705 --> 00:01:31,595
It does not automatically become authority.

25
00:01:31,595 --> 00:01:35,449
Codex compares the update with every active
conclusion.

26
00:01:35,449 --> 00:01:41,229
Six gates validate scope, evidence, complete impact,
action semantics, and shadow authority.

27
00:01:41,229 --> 00:01:43,637
Nothing changes before human review.

28
00:01:44,187 --> 00:01:47,857
A corrective resolution is the harder test.

29
00:01:47,857 --> 00:01:51,527
The original winner and loss explanation change.

30
00:01:51,527 --> 00:01:54,149
The award rule remains valid.

31
00:01:54,149 --> 00:01:59,392
The result matches the versioned reference and
cannot promote itself.

32
00:01:59,942 --> 00:02:04,248
The enforcement is measured: 49 tests and 23 golden
scenarios.

33
00:02:04,248 --> 00:02:08,555
It includes 6 lifecycle, 15 composition, and 6
impact gates.

34
00:02:08,555 --> 00:02:12,000
The harness admitted 0 of 8 injected faults.

35
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:15,445
This capture retains three real Codex Session IDs.

36
00:02:15,995 --> 00:02:20,880
Codex accelerated architecture, implementation,
testing, and production diagnosis.

37
00:02:20,880 --> 00:02:26,987
TenderGraph gives companies an agentic bidding team
with governed memory.

38
00:02:26,987 --> 00:02:32,483
Agents can discover, qualify, prepare, check,
monitor, and learn.

39
00:02:32,483 --> 00:02:36,758
GPT-5.6 can reason. Humans remain the authority.
